---

## **ğŸ”§ Emergency Fix Commands**

### **If App is in src/ Directory:**
```bash
# Move everything from src/ to root
mv src/app ./
mv src/components ./
mv src/lib ./
mv src/hooks ./
mv src/interfaces ./
mv src/services ./
mv src/*.ts ./
mv src/*.js ./
mv src/*.json ./
rmdir src

# Update import paths
find . -name "*.ts" -o -name "*.tsx" | xargs sed -i 's|from "src/|from "./|g'
```

### **Verify Structure Before Deployment:**
```bash
# Check these exist in root
ls -la app/page.tsx components/ lib/ package.json next.config.js
```

---

## **ğŸ“‹ Pre-Deployment Checklist**

- [ ] `app/` directory in root
- [ ] `package.json` in root
- [ ] `next.config.js` in root
- [ ] `components/` in root
- [ ] `lib/` in root
- [ ] No `src/` directory with app files
- [ ] All imports use relative paths
- [ ] `vercel.json` uses standard config

---

## **ğŸš¨ Warning Signs**

- `"No Output Directory found"`
- `"Configure the Output Directory"`
- Next.js app in `src/` directory
- Custom build commands in `vercel.json`

---

## **âœ… Deploy Command**
```bash
vercel --prod
